'''Bilge Khagan''' ([[Old Turkic language|Old Turkic]]: [[File:Old Turkic letter N1.svg|10px]][[File:Old Turkic letter G1.svg|10px]][[File:Old turkic letter Q.png|10px]] [[File:Old Turkic letter A.svg|10px]][[File:Old Turkic letter G2.svg|10px]][[File:Old Turkic letter L2.svg|10px]][[File:Old Turkic letter I.svg|10px]][[File:Old Turkic letter B2.svg|10px]], Bilge qaÎ³an)<ref name="irq.kaznpu.kz">[http://irq.kaznpu.kz/?lang=e&mod=1&tid=1&oid=16&m=1 Bilge kaganâ€™s Memorial Complex, TÃœRIK BITIG]</ref> (683 or 684 â€“ 734) was the [[khagan]] of the [[GÃ¶ktÃ¼rks#Second Turkic Khaganate|Second Turkic Khaganate]]. His accomplishments were described in the [[Orkhon inscriptions]].

==Names==

As was the custom, his personal name and the name after assuming the title Khagan were different. His personal name was : é˜¿å²é‚£é»˜æ£˜é€£, AshÇnÃ  mÃ²jÃ­liÃ¡n, a-shih-na mo-chi-lan) . His name after assuming the title was Bilge Khagan (or Bilge Qhagan). ([[Old Turkic]]: {{OldTurkicUnicode|ğ°‹ğ°ƒğ° ğ°ğ°€ ğ°´ğ°ğ°£}}, Bilge qaÎ³an,<ref name="irq.kaznpu.kz"/> [[wikt:æ¯—|æ¯—]][[wikt:ä¼½|ä¼½]][[wikt:å¯|å¯]][[wikt:æ±—|æ±—]], [[Pinyin]]: pÃ­jiÄ kÄ›hÃ n, [[Wade-Giles]]: p'i-chia k'o-han, official title: {{OldTurkicUnicode|ğ±…ğ°­ğ°¼ğ°ƒğ±…ğ° ğ±…ğ°­ğ°¼ğ°ƒğ°“ğ°€ ğ°‰ğ°†ğ°ğ°¢ğ± ğ±…ğ°‡ğ°¼ğ°œ ğ°‹ğ°ƒğ° ğ°ğ°€ ğ°´ğ°ğ°£}}, TeÅ‹Ñ–riteg Ğ¢eÅ‹iride bolmuÅ¡ TÃ¼rÃ¼k Bilge qaÎ³an,<ref>[http://irq.kaznpu.kz/index.php?l=t&wi=726&lang=e&mod=3 Ethno Cultural Dictionary, TÃœRIK BITIG]</ref> His wife was [[Po Beg]], [[Tonyukuk]]'s daughter. "Bilge" sounds similar to Mongolian language word "bileg" meaning "gift/present/lucky." Gift, presenty, lucky is Beleg in Mongolian not Bileg.  Bileg means intelligence and wise in Mongolian.

==As a khagan==
In 716, [[Kapaghan Khagan]] the second khaghan of the khaganate was killed in his campaign against [[Tokuz-Oguzes|Toquz Oghuz]] and his severed head was sent to [[Chang'an]].<ref name="Tang194">''[[Book of Tang]]'', [[:zh:s:èˆŠå”æ›¸/å·194ä¸Š|Vol. 194-I]]</ref> Although his son [[Inel Qaghan]] succeeded him, the legal claimant of the throne was his cousin AshÇnÃ  mÃ²jÃ­liÃ¡n. Mojilan's brother [[Kul Tigin]] and [[Tonyukuk]] carried out a [[coup d'Ã©tat]] against Inel Qaghan. They killed Inel Qaghan and made Mojilan a khagan with the name Bilge Qaghan.<ref name="Tang194"/> His name literally means "wise king".

Bilge's khaganate spanned vast steppes from the [[Caspian Sea]] to [[Manchuria]]; he also invaded the western sections of the [[China|Chinese]] territories. After his death from poisoning, several [[stela]]e were erected in [[Orkhon Valley|the capital area]] by the [[Orkhon River]]. These [[Orkhon inscriptions]] are the first known texts in the [[Old Turkic language]].
He was poisoned by Buyruk Chor<ref>[http://mtad.humanity.ankara.edu.tr/IV-3_Eylul2007/240_47_MTAD4-3_EEkrem.pdf Erkin Ekrem, "SarÄ± UygurlarÄ±n KÃ¶keni", ''Modern TÃ¼rklÃ¼k AraÅŸtÄ±rma Dergisi'', Vol. 4, No. 3, 2007, p. 175.]</ref> (æ¢…éŒ„å•œ/æ¢…å½•å•œ, mÃ©ilÃ¹ chuÃ², mei-lu-ch'o). He didn't die immediately and he had time to punish the family of Buyruk Chor with death.<ref name="Tang194"/>

